- Descriptive test cases
    Test cases descriptions should be shown to standard output. Figure out the best method of
    displaying these descriptions to the user.

- Exhaustive error messages
    The error messaging system needs to be worked so that errors can be understood and located with
    ease

- Add better documentation

- Replace relevant macros with inline functions
    Many macros increases the likelihood of having unintentional functionality such as supplying i++
    as an argument which could be used multiple times. Use inline functions to reduce these cases
    wherever possible.
